<seg id="190">The customs authorities checked the required data and notified the outcome of the investigation to the other member country via ELO.</seg>
<seg id="191">6. Summary</seg>
<seg id="192">The cooperation of the SAO-Czech Republic and the SAO of the Slovak Republic made it possible to compare the basic legislation governing the field of excise duties in the two states, the procedure of the Customs Authorities of the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic in the opening and closing of the transport of products under the conditional exemption regime between the two states, the registration of these traffic, and to further compare the exchange of information between customs authorities in the framework of international cooperation.</seg>
<seg id="193">6.1 Comparing the legislation governing excise duties in the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic, differences were found:</seg>
<seg id="194">(a) the procedure followed by the tax authorities and the tax authorities in commencing the transport of products under the conditional exemption scheme.</seg>
<seg id="195">The transport of products under the conditional exemption regime can only be initiated by a tax entity in the Czech Republic with the approval of the tax administration, which authorises the commencement of the transport on condition that the transported products have been provided with a tax guarantee equal to the tax attributable to them.</seg>
<seg id="196">The commencement of the transport of products under the conditional exemption scheme in SR is not subject to the authorisation of the tax authorities.</seg>
<seg id="197">During the audited period, the taxpayer was required to notify the tax authorities of the start of the transport of ethyl alcohol and tobacco products.</seg>
<seg id="198">He could start the transport of mineral oils, beer and wine without informing the tax authorities.</seg>
<seg id="199">In 2006, amendments to all excise laws were progressively adopted in SR, under which the consignor of goods under a duty suspension arrangement is required to send a copy of copy No 1 of the accompanying document electronically or by fax to the customs office of local authority of the consignor before commencing transport;</seg>
<seg id="200">(b) within the time limits for dispatching copy No 3 of the accompanying document.</seg>
<seg id="201">The recipient in the Czech Republic is obliged to send copies No 3 and No 4 of the accompanying document to the tax authority for verification at the latest on the following working day after the transport is completed.</seg>
<seg id="202">The certified copy No 3 shall be sent to the consignor at the latest on the following working day following receipt from the tax authorities.</seg>
<seg id="203">The recipient in SR is required to send to the consignor of the products copy No 3 certified by the tax authorities and the consignee of the products no later than the 15th day of the month following the month in which he received the goods.</seg>
<seg id="204">6.2. Customs authorities in both SR and the Czech Republic keep an electronic register of shipments of products under the conditional exemption regime.</seg>
<seg id="205">The content and method of keeping such records are not regulated by law in the Czech Republic or the Slovak Republic.</seg>
<seg id="206">Customs authorities in both countries record all the data from the accompanying documents on the basis of which the transport is carried out.</seg>
<seg id="207">There is currently no single electronic system for monitoring the transport of goods under a duty suspension arrangement between the Member States of the European Union, allowing excise duty managers in each Member State to obtain real-time information on the transport of goods.</seg>
<seg id="208">Under Decision 1152/2003/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 16 June 2003, the introduction of an electronic system to monitor the movement of excisable products is foreseen from 1 July 2009.</seg>
<seg id="209">On the basis of the agreement on cooperation in control activities, the Czech side handed over to the Slovak side a database of the transport of products under the conditional exemption scheme started in SR and terminated in the Czech Republic.</seg>
<seg id="210">The database included 5,876 items relating to transported mineral oils, ethyl alcohol and tobacco products.</seg>
<seg id="211">The Slovak side handed over to the Czech side a database of the transport of products under the conditional exemption scheme initiated in the Czech Republic and terminated in SR.</seg>
<seg id="212">The database included 3,319 items relating to transported mineral oils, ethyl alcohol and tobacco products.</seg>
<seg id="213">The Czech side compared the data for shipments listed in the register of shipments initiated in the Czech Republic with the record of shipments terminated in the Slovak Republic.</seg>
<seg id="214">The Slovak side compared data on the transport of goods under the conditional exemption regime initiated in the Slovak Republic and terminated in the Czech Republic.</seg>
<seg id="215">Data reconciliation was hampered by the fact that the quantities of goods being shipped were not uniformly reported in the databases.</seg>
<seg id="216">In cases where it was not possible to clearly attribute data on individual traffic in the two registers, an examination of the accompanying documents was carried out and neither breaches of the conditional exemption scheme nor cases of tax evasion were found.</seg>
<seg id="217">On the basis of the findings of the parallel controls, it can be concluded that Member States can obtain valuable information from the traffic register to improve the management of excise duties.</seg>
<seg id="218">The setting up of an electronic system for the movement and control of excise goods within the meaning of Decision No 1152/2003/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council will allow for the electronic transmission of the accompanying document and more effective control of movements under suspension of excise duty within the territory of the European Union.</seg>
<seg id="219">Communiqué</seg>
<seg id="220">This report was prepared in Czech, English and Slovak.</seg>
<seg id="221">The report was signed by the President of the Najvyšší Audit Office of the Slovak Republic and the President of the Supreme Audit Office, Czech Republic.</seg>
</p>
