<seg id="620">Cooperation between them has revealed differences in the strategies for detecting VAT fraud cases as well as differences in the above areas of VAT administration in the Czech Republic and Germany.</seg>
<seg id="621">The control findings were compared and good practices were identified based on them.</seg>
<seg id="622">In addition, both SAIs hope that the results achieved will give a boost to stakeholders to start a discussion on approaches and strategies within Member States, including at European Commission level.</seg>
<seg id="623">The extremely valuable experience and knowledge gained from the cooperation between the two SAIs can serve as an encouragement for the implementation of future control actions in the field of VAT administration.</seg>
<seg id="624">6. Communiqué</seg>
<seg id="625">The report was drawn up in Czech, English and German and signed by the President of the Supreme Audit Office of the Czech Republic and the President of the Federal Court of Auditors (Bundesrechnungshof) of the Federal Republic of Germany.</seg>
<seg id="626">Release deadline: June 2010.</seg>
